## 1. Use Cases

### UC-169-01: Full-body Embedding During Indexing

**Actor:** System (Indexer)

**Main Flow:** 1. Indexer encounters a new/modified source file 2. Parse file with tree-sitter to extract function/method AST nodes 3. For each function: extract full body text from AST 4. If body <= 512 tokens: generate single embedding vector 5. If body > 512 tokens: chunk with 128-token overlap, embed each chunk 6. Store embeddings in vector index (sqlite-vec) with node\_id reference 7. Update graph node with embedding metadata (chunk\_count, total\_tokens)

**Alternative Flows:** - 2a. File exceeds max\_file\_size → skip entirely, log warning - 3a. Function body is empty (abstract/interface) → embed signature only - 5a. Body > 10K tokens → truncate to first 10K, log warning

### UC-169-02: Semantic Search with Body Embeddings

**Actor:** AI Agent / Developer

**Main Flow:** 1. User calls code\_search with natural language query 2. System generates query embedding 3. Search both signature vectors AND body vectors 4. Compute combined score: 0.3 \* sig\_similarity + 0.7 \* body\_similarity 5. Rank results by combined score 6. Return top-K results with file, function, similarity score

**Alternative Flows:** - 3a. Function has no body embedding (abstract) → use signature only (weight 1.0) - 4a. Query is short (< 5 tokens) → weight signature higher (0.6 sig + 0.4 body)

### UC-169-03: Persistent Graph Load on Startup

**Actor:** System (Server)

**Main Flow:** 1. Server process starts 2. Check for persistent graph database at .code-intel/index.db 3. Load graph metadata (version, last\_checkpoint, total\_nodes) 4. Verify graph version compatibility 5. Load graph into memory (nodes + edges + file index) 6. Server ready for queries (< 500ms total)

**Alternative Flows:** - 2a. No persistent graph exists → perform cold start (full index) - 4a. Graph version incompatible → discard, perform cold start - 5a. Graph corrupted (checksum fail) → discard, perform cold start, log error

### UC-169-04: Incremental Update on Startup

**Actor:** System (Indexer)

**Main Flow:** 1. After loading persistent graph, scan workspace files 2. For each file: compare mtime against stored file\_index 3. If mtime changed: compute content hash (FNV-1a) 4. If hash differs: mark file for re-indexing 5. Re-parse marked files, update graph nodes/edges 6. Re-embed modified functions (full-body) 7. Remove nodes for deleted files 8. Save updated graph checkpoint

**Alternative Flows:** - 3a. mtime same → skip (no change) - 4a. Hash same despite mtime change (touch) → skip - 7a. File renamed (same hash, new path) → update path, keep embeddings

### UC-169-05: .codeintelignore Filtering

**Actor:** System (Scanner)

**Main Flow:** 1. Before scanning a directory, check for .codeintelignore file 2. Parse ignore patterns (gitignore syntax) 3. Merge with parent directory patterns (cascading) 4. For each file in directory: check against merged patterns 5. If file matches ignore pattern → skip entirely (no parse, no embed, no graph) 6. If file matches negation pattern → include despite parent ignore

**Alternative Flows:** - 1a. No .codeintelignore in directory → use parent patterns + defaults - 2a. Parse error in .codeintelignore → log warning, use defaults only

## 2. Business Rules

|  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- |
| ID | Rule | Rationale |
| BR-169-01 | Body embedding weight = 0.7, signature weight = 0.3 for search ranking | Bodies contain more semantic information |
| BR-169-02 | Chunk size = 512 tokens with 128-token overlap | Optimal for MiniLM model context window |
| BR-169-03 | Warm startup must complete in < 500ms | User experience — instant availability |
| BR-169-04 | Content hash (FNV-1a) determines file change, not mtime alone | Handles touch/copy without content change |
| BR-169-05 | Default ignores always applied even without .codeintelignore | Common patterns (node\_modules, .git) should never be indexed |
| BR-169-06 | Child .codeintelignore overrides parent patterns | More specific rules take precedence |
| BR-169-07 | Graph checkpoint every 5 minutes during active indexing | Balance between durability and performance |
| BR-169-08 | Max body size for embedding = 10K tokens | Prevent memory issues with generated code |
| BR-169-09 | Functions < 3 lines get signature-only embedding | Trivial functions don’t benefit from body embedding |
| BR-169-10 | WAL mode required for concurrent read during write | Queries must work during incremental update |

## 3. Data Specifications

### 3.1 Embedding Storage Schema

**Table: embeddings**

|  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Column | Type | Description |
| id | INTEGER PK | Auto-increment |
| node\_id | INTEGER FK | Reference to graph\_nodes |
| vector\_type | TEXT | “signature” or “body” |
| chunk\_index | INTEGER | 0 for single, 0..N for chunked |
| embedding | BLOB | Float32 vector (384 dimensions for MiniLM) |
| token\_count | INTEGER | Tokens in this chunk |
| created\_at | TEXT | ISO timestamp |

**Table: file\_index**

|  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Column | Type | Description |
| path | TEXT PK | Relative file path |
| mtime | INTEGER | File modification time (epoch) |
| content\_hash | TEXT | FNV-1a hash of file content |
| size\_bytes | INTEGER | File size |
| last\_indexed | TEXT | ISO timestamp of last indexing |
| symbol\_count | INTEGER | Number of symbols extracted |

**Table: graph\_meta**

|  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Column | Type | Description |
| key | TEXT PK | Metadata key |
| value | TEXT | Metadata value |

Keys: version, last\_checkpoint, total\_nodes, total\_edges, schema\_version

### 3.2 .codeintelignore Format

# Comments start with #
# Glob patterns (gitignore syntax)
node\_modules/
build/
dist/
\*.min.js

# Negation (include despite parent ignore)
!build/generated-api/

# Directory-only pattern (trailing slash)
\_\_pycache\_\_/

# Wildcard patterns
\*.generated.\*
\*\*/vendor/\*\*

### 3.3 Chunking Algorithm

Input: body\_text (string), max\_tokens=512, overlap=128
Output: chunks (list of strings)

1. tokenize(body\_text) → tokens
2. if len(tokens) <= max\_tokens: return [body\_text]
3. chunks = []
4. start = 0
5. while start < len(tokens):
 end = min(start + max\_tokens, len(tokens))
 chunk = detokenize(tokens[start:end])
 chunks.append(chunk)
 start = end - overlap # overlap with previous chunk
6. return chunks

## 4. API Specifications

### 4.1 Enhanced code\_search Tool

**Endpoint:** MCP tool code\_search

**Input (unchanged interface, enhanced behavior):**

|  |  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| Parameter | Type | Required | Description |
| query | string | Yes | Natural language search query |
| limit | integer | No | Max results (default: 20) |
| file\_filter | string | No | Glob pattern to filter files |
| kind\_filter | string | No | Symbol kind filter (function, class, etc.) |

**Output (enhanced with body similarity):**

|  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Field | Type | Description |
| results[].file | string | File path |
| results[].symbol | string | Symbol name |
| results[].kind | string | Symbol kind |
| results[].score | float | Combined similarity score |
| results[].sig\_score | float | Signature similarity |
| results[].body\_score | float | Body similarity (new) |
| results[].preview | string | First 3 lines of body |

### 4.2 New reindex Tool

**Endpoint:** MCP tool reindex

**Input:**

|  |  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| Parameter | Type | Required | Description |
| force | boolean | No | Force full re-index (ignore persistent graph) |
| path | string | No | Re-index specific path only |

**Output:**

|  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Field | Type | Description |
| files\_scanned | integer | Total files checked |
| files\_updated | integer | Files re-indexed |
| files\_skipped | integer | Files unchanged |
| files\_ignored | integer | Files excluded by .codeintelignore |
| duration\_ms | integer | Total time |
| symbols\_total | integer | Total symbols in graph |

## 5. Processing Logic

### 5.1 Startup Sequence

|  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Step | Action | Max Duration |
| 1 | Open SQLite database | 10ms |
| 2 | Read graph\_meta | 5ms |
| 3 | Verify schema version | 1ms |
| 4 | Load file\_index into memory | 50ms |
| 5 | Load graph nodes (lazy) | 100ms |
| 6 | Load graph edges (lazy) | 100ms |
| 7 | Server ready | Total < 300ms |
| 8 | Background: incremental scan | Async (non-blocking) |

### 5.2 Incremental Update Algorithm

1. loaded\_files = read file\_index from DB
2. disk\_files = scan workspace (respecting .codeintelignore)
3. to\_update = []
4. to\_delete = []
5. to\_add = []

6. for file in disk\_files:
 if file not in loaded\_files: to\_add.append(file)
 elif file.mtime != loaded\_files[file].mtime:
 hash = fnv1a(file.content)
 if hash != loaded\_files[file].content\_hash:
 to\_update.append(file)

7. for file in loaded\_files:
 if file not in disk\_files: to\_delete.append(file)

8. Process to\_delete: remove nodes, edges, embeddings
9. Process to\_update: re-parse, update nodes/edges, re-embed
10. Process to\_add: parse, add nodes/edges, embed
11. Save checkpoint

## 6. Non-Functional Requirements

|  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Category | Requirement | Metric |
| Startup | Warm start | < 500ms for 50K symbols |
| Indexing | Full-body embedding throughput | >= 30 functions/sec |
| Search | Query response time | < 200ms |
| Storage | Disk usage | < 5x signature-only |
| Reliability | Crash recovery | No data loss (WAL) |
| Concurrency | Read during write | Supported (WAL mode) |

## 7. Error Handling

|  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Scenario | Severity | Behavior |
| Corrupt graph database | Critical | Discard, full re-index, log error |
| File too large for embedding | Warning | Skip body embedding, use signature only |
| .codeintelignore parse error | Warning | Use defaults, log parse error |
| Embedding model OOM | Critical | Reduce batch size, retry |
| Disk full during checkpoint | Critical | Abort checkpoint, keep in-memory state |

